predictions.article: The Trump administration has implemented a series of significant tariffs in early 2025, creating substantial economic ripple effects across global trade relationships.
predictions.prediction: The imposition of tariffs by the Trump administration will lead to a decrease in U.S. agricultural exports to China by at least 10% within the next two months.

predictions.article: The new tariffs announced in March 2025 are expected to have several significant economic consequences for Midwest farmers, creating a challenging environment for agricultural producers across the region.
